text:
Let us not forget that Chick fil a IS a fast food restaurant. In fact this is one of my youngest daughters favorite places to get a chicken sandwich; specifically The Spicy Chicken Sandwich. This sandwich has a kick to it that will excite your taste buds and potentially make your nose run.
The reason I am giving this eatery such a high rating is the service! They have the nicest young people staffing this place with great manners and they are so attentive to the customers. They are always VERY busy, but they manage to take your order and get your food to you quite quick. They even walk around and ask if you want your drink re-filled!! That is going above and beyond. My over-all impressions are that they keep the restaurant clean, friendly hard-working staff equals great customer service, and pretty good food (for fast food). I just have to mention this too.... They are closed on Sundays (the Lords Day) to give their employees this day to worship. If you don't like or perhaps totally love the owners politics/in your face family values that is a big consideration when contemplating eating here and spending your dollars here. #gaymarriage

I do not know what the fuss about this place. Okay, it is big. They have variety of food, mostly International foods. The deli is packed but they sell Boar's Head products like Publix :) I had the Sesame Tuna sandwich which was OK. I also tried Hot Italian sandwich and it was also OK. Their bread is pretty good. Good beer and wine selection. Again, this place sells no different stuff than Publix. Just little better decoration, that's all.

This is a casual pizza joint.  I needed a little something heartier than a slice of pizza, so I ordered the Veggie Roll.  I'm not sure what makes it a roll rather than a calzone other than it's shape, but it was delicious.  Their marinara is delicious, so I bet their pizza is awesome.  The veggies in the Veggie Roll were all fresh, not frozen or canned, and I always appreciate that.  The staff was friendly enough and my food was cooked really fast.  There weren't a lot of people in there, though, so I don't know how the wait is when it's packed.  I'll definitely be back to try the pie!

We came here around 7-8 pm and it wasn't busy at all, so they serve our table quick. Place look very simple but clean. We tried chicken briyani and mixed grill platter. So first of all both dishes are huge, so easily can share. Briyany was too spicy for me so I worked on grilled platter. Lamb chops were just awesome. Juicy, soft and flavorful. Very good, 4 stars!

Run by the same people as Knifewear next door, this is definitely a "man's store" stocked with every kind of shaving supply imaginable, particularly items for straight-blade shaves. There is also a large selection of axes and knives for camping or outdoor work. The staff seemed knowledgable and friendly. A great place to get gifts for the men in our lives.
The hotel is nice, location is situated around restaurant chains and supermarket, with in walking distance, which is a plus for me.

By far, my go to spot when I come to Nawlins!  I'm a regular here not because the food is great (Which it is!)  But in the past three years that I've been coming here on my business trips, this is the only restaurant in which the staff remains consistent!

If there is any turn-over, it is very minimal!  I've gotten to know the owner and staff pretty well and they are very accommodating.

In my opinion, this is one of New Orleans' secret gems!  Keep up the great work guys!
Capo is the best! They've been around for a long time, authentic, friendly place.  Toasted Italian Sub with the works!  Spumoni Ice Cream yummy.

Supervisor is a bitch but I still love the place! I try to avoid it when certain people are working to get away from the pretentious attitude (not sure where they get it- they're line cooks at fast food restaurant) but overall I like this place :-)

Ok scratch that- supervisor is a HUGE BITCH! Wow. I will not be coming here while she is working again.

Jon's Bar & Grille is becoming one of my favorite places to frequent. The atmosphere is laid back, there is closed off outside seating (upstairs & down) & the food is really good. The biggest draw for me is the always changing craft beer menu. The best part is the bartenders are very knowledgable in regards to the beer selection.

food was bland, outdated, and expensive.  this is not an innovative restaurant.  octopus was chewy, rubbery, tasteless, and lacked any grilled flavor.  

we had the blue fish which was like a greasy fishy stew.  everything was just pretty awful. 

sad we wasted our money there.  definitely do not recommend to anyone.

i walked over at 645 on a sunday evening to pick up some noodles on my way home. 55 minutes later i left without my noodles having been harassed by an incredibly rude manager and having paid my bill 2 minutes after arriving as asked. i pity his poor abused staff. the boss was determined to serve everyone who's order came in but had a seat before i got my silly noodle bowl. really? had i been told that that was the policy upon arrival i obviously would have thanked them  and left. they kept saying almost ready....  inexcusable. shame on him!

Man do they know good mexican. I would highly recommend the Short rib tamale. It was insanely flavorful and I wish I hadn't filled up on cerviche and guac before it came out, but those were excellent too so no harm no foul.

Love how they do the checklist for the guac. Getting to try guac with chipotle and oaxaca cheese was a whole new experience of guac and I loved every second of it. The cerviche was also very tasty. Think the crab one was a bit more flavorful than the other ones but they were both enjoyable. Presentation was pretty, margaritas plentiful, service lovely. This place wins in my book.

I'm a fan.

I dont give a hoot about English soccer but that's ok. I do however think their food is worth the background noise and cramped space you have to deal with to get it. I even sat in the back 3 feet from the toilet. It was stinky.

Because of the noise, hit or miss service, and cramped space, I didnt give it 5 stars. The food, however deserves it.

The fish and chips are in the top 5 I have ever had. Great breading and huge portion for 7.95! Even better than that is the gorgonzola pear sandwhich. It sounds weird but it is heaven. A big piece of salty rasher bacon compliments the pear and cheese. $6.95! 

They have local Sunking Ales and Lagers. I went with the JAVA Stout. Very heavy and dark but good. Coffee and beer together. What a treat.
The bacon avocado sandwich is like heaven in your mouth. $4.50 a sandwich. Awesome selection of drinks. The one downside is that it's cash only.

Great bar with great bartenders. What else can you ask for?

Blend is a nice upscale bar with a great patio along with great drink specials and a very good crowd. Inside is a little small, but there is enough standing room when it gets to that point. 

The outside area is nice with more seating as well as a patio bar that is open during busy nights. 

They offer a great Happy Hour special Monday-Friday as well as nightly specials during the week. The shuffleboard table is always a hit.

This elegant yet plain bakery boasts some of the best baked goods I have EVER had bar none! 

You are greeted by a very clean store & friendly staff with minimal decor - none is needed - the beautiful baked choices are art in themselves! 

After oooh'ing and aah'ing, we decided on a Butterfingers brownie bar that was so decadent, a perfect giant slightly sugared peanut butter cookie and a mini densely delish cheese cake. 


Although I cannot frequent this gem too often as I 
Value fitting in my clothes, I will periodically treat myself here, spread the Devine word and surprise family at Thanksgiving with yumminess!!!!

    YOU HAVE TO TRY THIS BAKERY!!!

We drove way out of our way to get here and to be honest the drive wasn't worth it. No one explained the menu to us, the service was only okay and the food was also only okay...
I would not go out of my way to eat here and I definitely will not go back.

My care at Temple has been so great that I am very hesitant to go outside of the system for any doctor. I also work for the organization and believe in the judgement of the professionals here. I've seen how much they place the patient at the center of what they do. Since moving from Massachusetts to Philadelphia, I've received care from some organizations and cannot compare the care and attention I receive at Temple to anywhere else.

I spent most of last week at my sister's house in Claymont and wanted to try one of Rigatoni's supposedly "famous" crab cakes. Last Wednesday (02/10), my brother-in-law and I ordered two entrees for pickup: I got the 4 oz. Crab Cake Platter with a Mediterranean salad, and he got the Supreme Crab Combo with a Crab Pretzel. Although I enjoyed my crab cake, I wasn't too thrilled with the Mediterranean salad; I thought I was going to get an actual salad and instead I got pasta salad in an odd-tasting peppery sauce (?). Also, I wasn't too keen on the price. $8.99 for a small-ish crab cake is a bit steep in my opinion. I understand good crab meat can be expensive, but I have a feeling Rigatoni's tends to lean towards the high end of the pricing scale for no other reason than the fact that they have no competition. 

My brother-in-law wasn't entirely pleased with his meal. He said it was "all right", but then felt nauseous afterwards. He was sick for most of the evening nursing a queasy stomach. My sister tried some of the Crab Pretzel and started feeling sick late that evening into the next morning. Maybe there were some pieces of crab that weren't exactly fresh in that pretzel or in my brother-in-law's meal, but I do know that my crab cake was very good, and the pieces of the Crab Pretzel I ate didn't give me any digestive problems. Still, it's disconcerting that two out of three people who ate something from this establishment got sick. I don't like playing stomach roulette when I go out to eat.

Fantastic customer service both wholesale shopping and auto services. My tire was flat once and the mechanics went above and beyond (truly!) trying to fix it but eventually I had to get it repaired at a full service shop. The Costco employee felt bad and even offered to partially reimburse me for something that broke when they were trying to fix my tire (I turned them down but it's the thought that counts!). I will never forget how kind and hard they were trying to help me!

Saturdays and Sundays are the days my boyfriend and I like to shop here because of all the delicious samples. The employees are all helpful, cheerful, and respectful. Place is clean, you'll find bargains, and produce is fresh and generally more healthy than what you find elsewhere. Some of the generic Costco (Kirkland signature) items are just as good if not better than brand names.

Best of all, I hear you don't even need a membership to eat at their food court with bargain prices. $1.50 for a hotdog and a drink with free refills? $10 for a delicious WHOLE 18" pizza? Too good to be true and yet it is!

With competitive prices, gas prices usually the lowest on gas buddy, and membership perks, such as travel getaway packages, I found I have always made back my membership fee and then some with the end of the year reward coupon. Can't say enough good things about this place and the company. Big fan!
Driest chicken known to man. Its like chicken jerky! And pricey.

I have been searching for a good salon in Philadelphia for years, and this place is the real deal.  I have been to Adolf Biecker multiple times for cut, color and brows and love everything about the place.

I love their Turkey Burgers, Turkey Chili, Garden Salads etc. The owner works behind the register daily. They fax menus to your job and if you live/work in the CBD area, they will deliver. I think this place is well needed in New Orleans, it should be well deserved and frequented if we want to keep it open.

This is a great place for vegans, vegetarians, pescetarians, flexetarians etc etc etc

Just OK. I needed to go to cherry hill mall and as it was my first time there I asked guest services where I should grab lunch. This was the suggestion. 

The greeted me kindly and I opted to sit at the bar. The bartender was friendly, allowed me to try the wine before committing but when I wanted him, he was usually nowhere to be found. 

They do have great lunch specials and I ended up with the salmon bento box. As the bartender said it is a lot of food, soup, salad, salmon and asparagus. I get the idea of a "bento box" but they brought all this out on 4 plates at the same time..I would have at least preferred my soup or salad to come first...by them all coming at once the soup and salmon were cold by the time I finished the salad. 

The soup (clam chowder) nothing special...I had a few bites. The salmon was cooked how I requested and came on a bed of mashed potatoes which I tried not to eat but they were buttery and delicious. 

Portion sizes at lunch are small but with the salad and the asparagus I left full.  Definitely nothing to write home about, just another chain restaurant.

A bit out of the way, I'll make the drive up the 154 on a Sunday for a lovely view and go to Cold Spring Tavern for their tri-tip sandwich, relaxed atmosphere, and to enjoy live music with friends. Parking for your car and for your rear are often limited, but definitely doable. The rustic charm coupled with the 98% chance there'll be a good dose of sunlight dappling through the tree tops as you dine will convince you that this ought to be your new Sunday tradition.

The Bluffs on Broadway is a very unique event space located on the river bluff, just south of downtown St. Louis and the Anheuser Busch Brewery.  It holds about 75 seated at tables and/or 200 for a cocktail party.  The interior is contemporary with lots of whimsical art.  They have several decks, including two  that overlook the Mississippi river.

My only complaints about BOB is that parking is limited and it is pricey to rent/feed your guests.  However, if you have the budget and want something unique, you won't be disappointed.

Food was so so.. Split some apps with coworkers, Brussels sprouts were good... We were not aware there were not free refills on fountain drinks and rang up a $20 bill on club soda, very annoying.  We were also freezing the whole time

I don't think I could say enough good things about Lüke. We were originally trying to grab lunch at another place in New Orleans that ended up being completely full so we came into Lüke as a back up option and it was probably the best decision of my life. The meal was probably one of the best I've ever had and we came back twice during our six day stay. 

Must orders are the brussel sprouts, shrimp and grits, and the stuffed Bienville oysters. The brussel sprouts are charred perfectly and cooked in this delicious smoky sauce. The shrimp and grits were also sublime with an excellent balance of spices. The oysters were by far everyones favorite - they're cooked and served with a mix of shrimp and crab and a breadcrumb/cream topping. I would recommend going for lunch/dinner over breakfast as their breakfast menu isn't as extensive but if you do go for breakfast I'd recommend the fried chicken and biscuit. It comes with a tobasco honey sauce that is so delicious.

The prices are extremely reasonable and you can enjoy a nice cocktail while there as well. Couldn't recommend this place enough and it's generally pretty easy to get a table (we didn't have a reservation either time and only waited 10 mins max).

I love this place! Ice cream is arguably my favorite food, so as long as a store offers great service and a variety of flavors, I am happy & Goody's did not disappoint. This place was recommended to me by several coworkers and I have been twice now. The 1950's ice cream parlor feel is awesome & it takes you back in time. I have loved the ice cream & will definitely be back soon!

Frost Gelato is a blessing to Tucson for all those who enjoy gelato. I'm not going to pretend like it's comparable to anything you'll find in Italy, because let's face it, nothing in the US really will be (except for maybe some hidden gems scattered across the country perhaps). However, for a small chain, Frost gets the job done. Friendly servers willing to let you sample any flavors you want, generous scoops for each cup size, and a variety of different and interesting gelato flavors. Honestly, it's hard not to want to keep coming back once you've been there once.

This place gets five stars hands down best pizza best delivery service this business is how other businesses should look at on how to run one. Grew up here as a kid and moved back here it's been 2 years I know about all the pizza spots around Delaware county and New Jersey this place is pizza is one of the best the white with broccoli tops mackomanko in jersey if you know the place on the boardwalk everyone thrives on around here most of all this place is professional great all around food from the cheese steak egg rolls to the fries. Hope this helps because I'm always on here trying to find good places to eat *yelp* and this place deserves the attention for good food and good delivery service and business!
Delicious food and great staff. Alicia was friendly, knowledgeable, and went out of her way to make my dining experience a great one.  I will definitely be back!!!
Another burger joint in town.  Burger and fries eaten were OK.  I will return to try the signature milk shakes

What can I say, I am a total fan. 

When they first opened, there were a few missing touches with their drinks but they quickly found their mojo.

I have visited the Truckee location before and that's where I tried their Cheddar Scallion Scone and oh my, it was a-ma-zing. So when I found out that they were coming to Reno, I was ecstatic. The only downside was they stopped making this pastry maybe a month after they opened their Reno location. I was really bummed. The barista I asked said that it was just not selling. I told her they can just make it for me and I will buy them all -- wishful thinking. I soon tried the Raspberry Ricotta Scone and this has been my new fave. I still wish that one day they would bring my old-school favorite back.

All in all, they have great pastries and sandwiches. Their crepes are also very tasty and they are huge, at least for me. Make sure to try the Espresso Chocolate Bar -- I have never had anything like this before. Another suggestion is the Lemon Ricotta Cookie -- you can totally taste the fresh lemons that were used for this goodness. My favorite sandwich is the Milano. The chipotle sauce (I think that's whats in there) is quite tasty with a tangy, spicy after taste.

As for drinks, I have absolutely loved their mate lattes. I think they are they only one in town that serves mate lattes but I could be totally wrong. I don't really drink coffee and am more of a tea drinker, which makes the mate lattes the perfect drink for me.

If you are around the area, this is a must-try for sure. Their decor is very welcoming, they added a "community table" that is quite impressive. Lots of room for meetings and small gathering. Oh, they have gelato too. Nutella gelato of all else. One word - Yummy.

I mean, what can you say. The place is a kitchy nasty chain. It's so plastic, its like... Las Vegas plastic. The menu is meager, but the shakes aren't bad. I just can't validate going into this place when you're on South Street, with TONS of choices around.
Quiet, good service, good fish, standard (boring and tasteless) app and salad, nice decor, good menu. Would go back. Would avoid the salad. Happy hour M-Th 5-7 drinks and appetizers.

Came here for A quick bite to eat with the family trying to avoid places like Taco Bell. I wanted to check and quesadilla and I must say it was really good better than I expected. Everybody was happy no complaints and when I checked in the app rewarded us with a free doughnut and I can't complain because their donuts are specialized and very good. Will definitely come back. The service was very fast and the environment was pretty clean. There was a small error on one of the orders but they were very quick to take it back and bring out the exact right order with no complaints and no hard time so it was very well-managed in my opinion.

I love this park been there a many times with my Ginger, recently I've encountered aggressive dogs which I've decided to take a break. My dog was bit in the face by a dog and the woman walked away with little to no care. I want to report this to the head of the park to make awareness of this type of behavior. Does anyone know where I would go for such?

We had a great experience buying an engagement ring at Gossage. We had gone into half a dozen other stores, and neither the jewelry nor the service felt quite right. The rings were beautiful, but the service was phenomenal. The lovely lady that helped us (Kim) was not pushy but was very attentive. She was really good at pulling out ring after ring for me instead of just waiting for me to point out specific ones. I felt like I could take a close look at a wide variety of rings when I didn't know exactly what I wanted. She was also great at finding things at our price range; at one point I found a couple I liked that were too expensive, so she isolated similar ones that were cheaper. We got a same-day sizing on the ring for free. We had a fantastic experience, thank you!!

I'm revising my original review from 1 to 3 stars.  I may have been a bit too harsh on my criticism.  After reading other Yelper's reviews, I decided to go back today with several coworkers. I came at this with a different frame of mind.  Zaxby's is not the place you go to eat healthy, nor do they claim to be.  I came at it as Zaxby's vs Chick-Fil-A.  And in that respect, I decided to revise my rating. 

I still prefer Chick-Fil-A, but there is a lot to like at Zaxby's. I got their Nibblers plate today, and also ordered cheese bites, fried pickles and Texas toast to share.  I still think the deep frier needs some work. The fries could be crispier.  The cole slaw was good, and I am a fan of the cheese bites. 

The chicken was good.  I find Chick-Fil-A's to be juicier.  But it wasn't bad at all, certainly not deserving of the 1 star review I gave it before. 

So, bottom line, although I expect to go to Chick-Fil-A more often, I would not hesitate to stop here if the opportunity presented itself.  I'm not quite a fan, but I'll say they are A-OK.

WOOT WOOT 
This place rocks!!
You can sit outside and enjoy a coffee, tea, or any beverage of choice.
They also have fresh pastries and breakfast sandwiches made daily. 
The best chai tea latte I have ever had. The sausage egg and chees on an English muffin is delicious as well. 
GO! you wont be disappointed

cheers,

Chipotle is the Targét of the Mexican fast food game. 

What's not to love about Chipotle?  Burritos (or tacos/ bowls) made your way. Quick. Hot. Fresh. Generally great service at this Cherry Hill location.  They also have a really good soundtrack playing whenever I go in. 

My go to is the carnitas burrito but you can't really go wrong with anything.  Good rice, fresh salsa and guacamole.  

And yes, we are aware the guacamole is extra. 

As for the price, it's a bit more expensive than your normal fast food joint, but then again the quality and freshness is a step up.

santa barbara shellfish company wow great seafood very fresh and tasty try the uni with scallops wow the uni was really fresh still alive and moving on top of the fresh scallops wow some thing u must try it was so good that i end up getting 2 uni the grill lobsters wow fresh from the water then grilled some tasty stuff very very tasty the steamers clams wow also really fresh and tasty plus they got a good selection of craft beers check them out santa barbara shell fish company good eats yelp on yelpers

I decided to try the grooming salon, I have to have someone who's good with Rottweilers and after talking with the staff one day they gave me the name of a gal who is very good with this breed. I was able to get a next day appointment on Saturday! When I met her, she was very helpful and professional. My Rottie let her clip her claws  (She's particular about that) and she looked and smelled gorgeous! Unlike Petsmart, you can't get cash back when you go to pay for services and you can't put a tip on there,  so make sure you bring cash for a tip.
Fish Tacos were OK. But when you charge $4.95 to replace fries with fruit, that's just absurd.  And it would be helpful if the waiter noted the extra fee when we ordered.
Nice people and good food.  Great local neighborhood spot.  I eat there every time that I visit in Port Richmond.

I recently read somewhere that the best places to find ethnic food are those unassuming restaurants without fancy names or signage that you find in strip malls. African Palace was fits that description perfectly. I went here a few months ago with my adventurous restaurant buddy who had heard great things about it. It's waaay out in the county, but if you are looking for a different place to shake up your dining experience, it's totally worth the drive.

I've never been to West Africa nor am I an expert in that type of cuisine, but the place screamed authenticity to me. Our very kind waiter recognized that we were first timers and made suggestions on what to order. We had a simple, delicious beef appetizer with onions and a fantastic sauce. My friend ordered a fish dish and I ordered beef, both of which were very different from anything I'd tasted before, and very tasty. If I'm ever in the area again I'll definitely go back to try the rest of their menu.

The first restaurant I've ever been to with a sink in the dining room.  Apparently to wash your hands after a messy crab meal.  The bartenders are old-school Philadelphia.  Lots of characters and of course crab-fries.  One of the better sports bars in Philly.  I'm sure I'll be back.

Beautiful building. I've drove by the Palladium so many times and admired the way it looks. It is a smaller theatre with seats in front of the stage as well as an upper seating area.

We attended for an orchestra symphony and the sound was very good. Like others have said, you can sit pretty much anywhere in the theatre and have a good view of the stage. Seats are not too comfortable (wooden and hard). 

Appreciated the audience (no camera flashes or recording), I really enjoyed our night. Parking was a bit tricky, we ended parking about 3-4 blocks away as the garage near the theatre was closed the night we came. Had fun though! Would recommend checking it out. They have a lot of cool shows coming up.

This is the best deal of any Japanese food joint "."  You can order anything you want on the menu all for 10.99 (lunch). Place is packed and service is a bit slow , and our server wasn't the sharpest tool in the shed. If your in a hurry for lunch , I wouldn't recommend this place. However the food is fresh and delicious. This is my new sushi spot !

I ordered the bento box and it was terrible. The food was bland, spring rolls were complete mush on the inside and the chicken teriyaki was dry. My wife ordered the chicken teriyaki entree because she wanted something easy that would be hard to screw up. Well the chef at Umi found a way to screw it up. The chicken was dry and bland. We had to shred the few chunks that weren't completely dehydrated and submerge them in soy & teriyaki sauce. We finally gave up and didn't eat the majority of our food. I'm not a food snob; this is actually the first restaurant review I've ever left. Our experience was so bad I felt compelled to leave this review. Save your money, go to Zushimaki instead. The service at Zushimaki might not be the best but at least the food is excellent.

I love this place! I have been coming here for coffee, breakfast, lunch and to study since I was in high school. For the most part, the people are very friendly. The food is good- I especially like the breakfast sandwiches, the soups, the burger, the chicken sandwich, the club and the chicken tenders. Their burger specials are often really great and creative. The iced tea and frozen coffee are delicious! It's a cute atmosphere with a few quieter tables upstairs and a few outside as well. A great place to grab a bite or a coffee!

I can't even lie when I say this place left me with the biggest smile ever! Between the incredible employees and manager (Smiley) and how outrageously flavorful and generously portioned the food was for the price, I definitely plan on going back. To those who love Greek food, this will set a new and delicious standard for you.

Had to try it as I needed a fix and was close by meeting a customer! Great roast pork and provolone for sure. Will be back to try the hand carved roast beef next time. Got take out but looks like good place to grab a beer!
The best Italian market outside of NYC!  We are so lucky to have this store in St. Petersburg. Everything they have is fantastic. The bakery, deli, pasta, butcher etc. the best!

I love this place and the fact that they have almond milk and gluten free bagels! Great place to study. However, whenever I get an iced coffee there's barely any ice in it so it melts quickly. When I've tried asking for more they told me they don't have enough to give me more...strange. So losing one star for that!
Soooooooooooo amazing. Best hair cut ever.

It's "OK".  I usually stop in here early in the morning when it's empty so I don't deal with the lines or crowds.  The customer service line can be long.

You can find most items here including food ...  refrigerated, frozen and canned.   Looks like they did away with the fresh veggies. 

The prices are better then most places.

Will I be back?  yes but only at the crack of dawn when it's empty :)

Honestly one of the best haircuts, if not the best, I've ever had.  Jeff was utterly phenomenal at his craft, and approached barbering as more of an art than a service.  I ended up just going for the whole experience, getting a pretty dramatic fade cut, followed by a full shave.  This place is definitely serves as the uber-masculine alternative to a salon, where a man is massaging your face and you don't feel at all weirded out by that.  I work in the clothing retail business, so this cut will be getting a good bit of looks throughout the next couple of weeks.  I have already recommended Jeff and this place to a handful of friends only a few hours after I left.  Keep being great, Green Hills Barber Shop.

God this place is amazing. The furniture is just isn't comparable to anything else in Edmonton. The furniture is just so different and I just adore everything in this store. I fell in love with a $3100 sectional and I'm hoping one day ill be able to afford it. The staff are so friendly and there are tons of different fabrics available for the furniture they have in the store. Everything in 29 Armstrong seems mismatched but still perfectly in place. I love how chic but still elegant the pieces are in this store and if I could afford to do so I would finish my entire home with pieces from here. I was happy to see their new location is much larger than where they previously were on 104st. If you are looking to furnish a trendy space, this is the place to go!

an all around solid sushi experience.  I don't come here too often as I feel like this place falls in between Edomasa and Arigato in price range, both of which I prefer to Ichiban.  All around solid choice if you are on the mesa and in the mood for sushi.

Wine selection is great for amatuer or wino expert. Our server could have been a sommelier, she was deliciously descriptive.  We came in after a long walk looking for something refreshing, I asked if they had a Moscato. They did not, however, the server was quick to describe similar flavors and help me pick the most appetizing wine. Apologetically, the title escapes me. Not being a white wine drinker, this was very helpful.

Enjoyed a $3 snack, which is indeed that, tiny snack, but delicious.  Also the Tuna sandwich with Kalamata Olives. A great addition to what could have been a seemingly dry sandwich. The salty olives leave you salivating for the next bite. on ciabatta bread, which was very soft - the way I like it on account of my TMJ. 

Atmosphere is urban chic for in or outside dining. Casual dinner or cocktails and apps before dinner best.

I absolutely love the sushi at Toki! The quality of the food (especially the sashimi) is fresh and great tasting. Every time we go we always get greeted by their friendly staff. 
It's a gem in the Carrollwood area that anyone who enjoys sushi should check out.

Had a great experience here. Hit breakfast offered which includes waffles, eggs, cereal etc. tons of variety. The room were spacious and clean. Around and 7-10 walk to Bourbon street. Across from Harrahs casino and numerous restaurants. Great location! Staff is great:)

Always Long Lines at Check-Outs, rare to find an employee that is helpful or even happy for that matter.

When a business has to hires someone to stand at the door and say Welcome, it gives me the feeling that their employees are not happy enough to say hello, good morning or anything unless they are getting paid to say it. 

It's not really convenient and the prices aren't much cheaper if at all, not sure why I torture myself, is their marketing that good.

((( Perceived Value, not really a value )))

Everyone knows about DiBruno Bros but Claudio's is a somewhat hidden gem. Maybe not as extensive a selection of cheeses but they have all the basics and more and I find their prices to be better. They do, however, have a much better selection of olive oils and vinegars in my estimation. The store is larger comparatively speaking so it doesn't seem quite as crowded when waiting in line during the weekend rush.

Prices aside, the Bridge is pretty awesome and luxurious when it comes to catching the latest blockbuster. Where else can you reserve a seat, drink a pre-movie cocktail, and snuggle with your friend or lover in cushy leather seats (with movable arm rests)? 

If at all possible, avoid this place on a Friday or Saturday night. All my memories involve gratuitous commentary from nearby movie-watchers, which can sometimes add or detract from the movie at hand. There's a time and place for everything though, and if anyone's seen M. Night Shyamalan's, The Happening, you'd understand why vociferousness was appreciated.

Friendly staff - yeah! Love the busy yellow and blue design in the room - very cheery.  

Helpful, as most rooms face in, meaning there is not a lot of natural light that gets into the rooms.

Stratus is the 10th floor roof bar/dance club, and Friday (and probably Saturday), they get pretty popular.  On the 8th floor, I could sense rather than hear, the background music, but it was a nice background noise, not offensive at all.

Comfortable lobby, fantastic location around the corner from the Liberty Bell and good food and coffee and in a safe location (important to note in a city like Phili).

My fave place to stay in Phili.

Heard about this place so had to come try it. I love Indian food. This restaurant is awesome. I had the chicken 65 app, lamb korma and chicken vindaloo each was excellent . Restaurant is beautiful inside and out.

If you are within 50 miles of this place, it is worth the drive for a coffee & home made pastry!!! One of my favorite coffee shops & "patisseries" in the world  I swear if I glance outside, I can see the Seine...

I always get the salted caramel latte, the chocolate croissant & the Nutella & banana croissant  It is heaven!

The food was good and our waiter Jeffery was super nice. It was a slow start to order but he was literally waiting on every table and making drinks. I would definitely come back, I hope they get Jeffery some help because he was doing it all!

Pieology keeps its 4-star rating with me. We had a party of eight last night; everyone was happy with their pizza. Portions are as generous as you want. I noted that the pepperoni was very good, authentic, unlike you get at some places. A bonus was the coupons, which lots of people used. e.g. a $5 pizza. Heckof a deal.

This is a large sports bar hat hits the right notes if loud music, multiple tv screens and bar food is your thing.  Think of this like any major sports bar but on steroids and louder. The beer menu is extensive and they have a full service bar.  The food menu is replete with all the usual favorites but they also have a large selection of oysters, lobster and crab.  Almost like this place is trying to be Philly, Maryland and Maine all on one.    We tried the recommended CRAB FRIES. We received a  heaping basket of fries covered in Lowrys season salt like stuff with two cheese dipping sides.  It was enough to feed 6 but it was nothing to write home about nor would I recommend unless you have low blood pressure and are trying to pump it up...SALTY!  Also, there is nothing crabby about them.  Don't let the name fool you. No crab meat, no crab flavor. Just a big ole basket of fries. 
We ordered the Italian pizza which was a cheese pizza with arugula and balsamic sauce.  It came with a very thin crust.  Perfect and yummy.  Big enough for two.  The service was average but enough.  Overall, a decent place to go have a few brews and some average bar food.  I bet this place rocks when the local teams are playing.

Pretty good. On the other hand, I am totally unconvinced there is any kind of "home cooking" going on here, which is implied in a really circumspect and roundabout way. When I mildly pressed the owners about recipes and ingredients, I got an odd mixture of sales pitch and something about the food actually coming from India. Judging from that, I think a very good part of what they offer, are the kinds of "heat and serve" or quick-prep prepackaged Indian dishes you can get at an Indo-Pak grocery or even Trader Joes. Really, its a great idea for what it is, kind of like a Hindu-Kush flavored Skyline Chili, but this is really and truly fast food.

My pork sandwich was delicious. They have a buy 4 get the fifth sandwich free deal. The boba was just ok. The pho left something to be featured in the flavor department. Overall, this place fits the bill for affordable quick authentic grub on the go. The television inside displayed cock fights just to let you know. (Very authentic) The restaurant seemed tidy, and the staff goes out of their way to make patrons feel comfortable, despite the obvious language barrier. I live their bahn mi, some day I'll have to come back!

Staffed exclusively by apathetic, dull-witted employees committed to helping you as little as is humanly possible. First one I asked for help wasn't even aware the business had closed 15 minutes before, which would have saved me some time; the second replied to a question about whether there were any other open car washes close by with "Do you know how to work GPS on your phone?" Absolute waste of time.

We were on a mission to find tacos al pastor after a great Vegas trip. This is where we ended up. The tacos were delicious (albeit not nearly as amazing as Tacos el Gordo). Service was super fast, tacos and salsas were tasty. No complaints!

This was the first meal on the first day of our visit to NOLA. We were prepared for a long wait but they had a table for us on a Friday evening as soon as our party of four got there! 

Took us a few minutes to figure out the system - order drinks and food at the bar, carry your drinks to the table, wait for the food to come out as it gets done. The Sazerac and Hurricane were obligatory on our first night. Didn't disappoint. 

The food. The menu is not too big, its all small plates with some good vegetarian, fish and meat selections. 

Falafel sliders were amazing. As were the lamb sliders. The Meyer lemon was not detectable in the Cesar salad but it was excellent. Grilled shrimp on polenta was very good with a dark sauce. 

Dessert - hazelnut cake with Nutella ice cream - was very dry and not on par with the food quality. 

The Royal Roses were playing that evening - couldn't have planned a better way to start off our NOLA visit.

I have never been so insulted and talked down to in my life. Michelle, I think that's her name it's on my receipt but she never introduced herself, was the rudest person I have ever given my money to in my life. When we sat down she was talking about personal issues with the barback loud enough for us to hear and I thought that was odd in and off itself. When she gave us our menus she said a few times "these menus are good for the next 30 seconds."  Sorry but either give us brunch or give us dinner menus and explain that the kitchen is in the midst of a shift change, don't make us feel pressured because you dropped menus that have an extremely short time limit. Instead of eating we decided to just get drinks. She let us know that the brunch menu libations were, her words, 2 for 1. We ordered a mimosa off the list and hung out. When we got get drinks they set two wooden tokens down but didn't reference the at all, so we didn't know what they were for.  Eventually ordered some food off the dinner menu to go. She was very non existent the whole time we were sitting at the bar, not attentive at all. When we asked for the bill I saw that both our drinks were on there. I asked about them and let her know about the 2 for 1 statement she said. She then proceeded to tell me it was buy one, get one and that's what the tokens are for. I told her that "buy one get one" and "2 for 1" are different and if we knew it was BOGO we would have ordered another drink (if she would have even paid attention to us).  After a little back and forth she said she would take care of it and that "they weren't trying to screw us."  She talked to us like we were the worst people on earth because she doesn't know how to explain her own restaurants policies. I work in an industry that has me visiting 10-15 bars/restaurants/hotels a day and I have never had a worse hospitality experience in my life. Tavern Management - this employee is losing you revenue left and right.  Not only is she not taking care of customers and grabbing reorders, she is turning people away for good. This treatment was so horrible and off putting that I am going to go out of my way to recommended against going to Tavern due to the disrespect we felt. Hopefully your floor managers recognize how bad she is and theyo do something about it because she is taking money out of your pocket every shift she works.
Awesome place! Had a create your own omelet, eggs whites with crab...DELISH!  Huge bowl of strawberries on the side, super fresh and ripe!  Great service as well.

Excellent little spot in Newbold! 

The restaurant is vibrantly painted and cheery. We started with chai (the fennel and ginger) which was comforting and delightful and not too sweet. We moved on to some chaat and the chicken of the day. 

Everything was tasty. The service was quite friendly and we are very glad to have this new addition in the area.

Ricardo's is pretty nice. Their customer service is really good. Their pizza is on point, and their poppers are on point too!!!!! You have to get them fresh. The pasta is good. I've only had their chicken Alfredo and the shrimp but, all all, very
 Very good!!

I thought it was a good stay and spa visit after purchasing a "customer appreciation" deal with two nights and other credits and discounts. I get the bill and find they still charge for the room and tried to charge me twice for a beverage in the room. The beverage charge was handled but the voucher was a scam and didn't include the room cost at all. I will spread the word and never come back. So much for a good first stay experience. The lady on the phone even gave me attitude. Note: I read the fine print three times or more to avoid this.

Food was okay at best.
Waiter was Missing most of the time.
Dessert was disgusting.
Bar/Drinks are fun and hopping.
This place has a nice breakfast. I like the Po Boy French Toast thing they do. Everything always seems fresh and prepared well. If you go try the fresh squeezed juices.
I know everyone raves about this place but the chicken biscuit was pretty gross. The chicken was undercooked and slimy and I couldn't finish it. I would not go back.

I love this place, if we ever order out it's always here.

I love their white pizza, chicken parm sandwich, and macaroni bites! Yum!!

Can be a little expensive depending on what you get, but it's the best pizza in the area. :) Love!

Food tasted decent . Portion size is below chipotle, that's saying something . Wait time is ridiculous. Staff was very friendly and helpful . 14$ for lunch and all I got was a bowl and a few chips with dip,  not recommended . Definitely a facade for the area it sits . I'll skip going forward .
ROACHES CRAWLING ON THE WALLS! Walk in and you'll slide all over the dirty, grease filled floors. OMG.

We enjoyed our entire experience.  The view is killer, i mean the best in Philly, and request a window table, as there are only a few.  The food and service did measure up on the two occassions I dined.  The kitchen is clearly talented and executes the menu very well.  Wines are a bit pricey, but hey this is Center City.  Go, even to just have drinks at the bar.
Great service and really cool event space! We had a wonderful time at the art show! So many very talented people!

A much needed attraction for Santa Barbara.  the venue has intrinsic entertainment. The bartender Olivia  is cute as a button and does her job above and beyond. Go listen or sing along and have a libation filled time!

what a gem! CS Tavern is an excellent destination date or family outing. On a windy road above Santa Barbara, the tavern is an actual old stagecoach stop. The original buildings sit in a picturesque lush creek hollow. 

Our food was great, well cooked high quality cuts of beef and venison served with fresh bread, well cooked asparagus, great salads, and killer garlic potatoes. we're not experts, but it seemed like a good selection of wine and we enjoyed our bottle.

It was pretty hot on the June night we were there. So hot in fact, we corked our bottle early and took it outside to finish it. The service was fine but not amazing.

Definitely worth the effort to check out this bit of California history!

I made my first visit to Blake's yesterday. I give it a 3.5. It's a great addition to the fast food scene here. A different, more hip vibe and a decent burger.  I love that their ketchup packets actually have a useful amount of ketchup in them. Free wifi is a plus, I used it and it worked great. The staff were friendly, and it seemed sincere; they seem happy to be working there.  The Lotaburger came with a substantial meat patty, that had good flavor and texture.  Two complaints.  The chocolate milkshake was bad.  It's the dreaded 'ice milk' from my childhood that the family would buy when we were on hard times financially.  A huge yuk, didn't even finish it.  Also, the Hatch green chiles were too hot.  I love hot, as evidenced by my high ratings for Poco and Mom's here in Tucson and for various NM food venues.  But this was ridiculous, just too much, which takes away from enjoying not only the chile but the hamburger.  I guess if frat boys want to get into a competition to survive high heat in their mouth, this is the place for them.  But the rest of us will have to make a more palatable green chile burger at home.  If I go again, and I might, I'll have a burger sans green chile and stick with a soda rather than the shake.

Moonshine me up, baby!

Stopped in with my friend for a quick drink since we had a few minutes to spare before meeting others down the street for dinner. Diablo's is very large would be a great place to go for some fun with a larger crowd maybe to catch a game or fight or even enjoy some live music.

The assortment of Moonshine caught our eye on this particular evening so I ordered a strawberry lemonade (strawberry moonshine) and M had a cherry coke (cherry moonshine). Both were actually really good and the alcohol was surprisingly tasty and not overpowering at all. But then our waitress gave us each a piece of fruit from our moonshine jars. Whoooeeeee! Definitely has a bite! 

I'd definitely come back to Diablo's. Looks like a fun spot!

Have been here multiple times for breakfast, brunch, and dinner. It has been great every-time.

The orange juice is freshly squeezed and is amazing! The service has also been great every-time. Every cocktail has been fantastic.

The outdoor seating is beautiful and has a lot of fans to keep it cool, even with the unrelenting heat of Florida's summers.

Will return many, many times, for great food, cocktails, and service.

Great Service, Great atmosphere and unbelievable toasted raviolis. 
Had a great experience, will definitely be back soon.

I have been getting my color and cut done at Salon L'Etoile Spa for 5 years now, and my stylist, Tammi, gets better with each visit.  My style and taste has varied through the years, and Tammi has always been able to replicate my ideal look.

The atmosphere at L'Etoile is laid-back and relaxing.  The staff takes great care of you from the moment you walk into the venue. 

Def recommend to book ahead, they get busy!

Being a national park....I was disappointed.  I was expecting better and more.  There's actually 2 parks.  A Saguaro East and a Saguaro West. The East had nothing. I spent an hour there and left.  The West was much better and it's right near Tucson Mountain Park which had scenic views. I didn't even see a place on Yelp to write a review for the East side, that's how quiet it is.

Both parks have roughly 8 - 10 mile driving loops where you can stop, take short hikes, explore the Saguaros and take in the atmosphere of a true desert. The West Park loop is called Bajada Loop Drive.

The East has Sonoran Desert Overlook, a Cactus Forest, Mica View, and Desert Ecology Trail which is about a half mile walk but nothing to see.

The West has 2 good, short little hikes w/ nice views of the desert and beyond. Valley View Overlook Trail was nice especially when I went early in the morning with the sun rising.  The other is Signal Hill Trail.  I took great pics from both trails.

I did watch a short 20 minute film about Saguaro National Park in the West side of the park.  It gives you a background about the Saguaros.

For a national park, Saguaro East and West isn't up there with the other well known parks. But if you're in Tucson, I'd definitely recommend spending 2 - 3 hours at the West side of the park.  Btw, both parks are roughly 20 - 30 miles from each other, on opposite sides of Tucson.  And it's $10 to get in.
